Usage: create_op_cond [-help] -P <processValue> -T <temperatureValue>
                      -V <voltageValue> -library_file <libraryFileName>
                      -name <virtualOpcondName>

-help                               # Prints out the command usage
-P <processValue>                   # Specifies the process value for the
                                    # operating condition (float, required)
-T <temperatureValue>               # Specifies the temperature value for the
                                    # operating condition (float, required)
-V <voltageValue>                   # Specifies the voltage value for the
                                    # operating condition (float, required)
-library_file <libraryFileName>     # Specifies the library for which to create
                                    # the virtual operating conditions
                                    # (string, required)
-name <virtualOpcondName>           # Specifies the name for the operating
                                    # condition being created (string, required)